A Javascript for Adobe Illustrator by James E. Talmage.\par
\tab\par
Purpose:\par
Creates a textFrame object that can be used as either just a reference and then deleted, or as a label in the drawing.\par
\tab\par
Schema:\tab\par
This script returns an alert containing the area of the frontmost selected pathItem.\par
The area is given in the five units of measure supported by Illustrator's rulers.\par
A pointType textFrame object is created at the center of the pathItem's bounding box\par
containing the text of the alert.\par
\par
To Use:\par
Select a path. Run the script. Delete, edit, and/or style the resulting textframe object as desired. \par
