\b JET_NumberedCallouts\b0\par
A Javascript for Adobe Illustrator CS2 by James E. Talmage.\par
\par
Purpose:\par
Creates a set of textFrame objects containing sequential numbers with an optional prefix.\par
Also names each object (names appear in the Layers Panel) by the prefix and number.\par
The naming portion of the script works on any object that can be duplicated. Therefore, the script can also be used to create and name a series of copies of any other type of object.\par
\par
To Use: Select one object. Run the script.\par
\par
\b JET_SerialNumbers.jsx\b0\par
A Javascript for Adobe Illustrator by James E. Talmage\par
\par
Purpose:\par
Creates serial numbers within a selected text frame, incremented by one, with user-defined prefix, number of entries, and starting number.\par
Numbers are separated by carriage returns. Useful for ticket-like number sequences.\par
\par
To Use:\par
Create a textframe object. This can be either PointType or AreaType. Select the textframe as an object.\par
(Do not have the text edit cursor active inside it.) Then run the script.\par
The content of the textframe is replaced by the serial numbers according to the parameters you specify in the prompts.\par
