\b JET_X_SwatchesLegend.jsx\b0\par
A Javascript for Adobe Illustrator by James E. Talmage.\par
\par
Purpose:\par
Creates a series of labeled squares at the bottom left of the Artboard, each filled with one Swatch in the Swatches Panel.\par
Useful for adding a "color legend" on pages of identity graphics, to specify colors.\par
\par
Algorithm:\par
For each named Swatch in the Swatches Palette, the script draws a square filled with the Swatch color,\par
and creates beside it a PointType object containing the name of the Swatch.\par
The text labels are filled with Registration color.\par
A prompt allows the user to set the desired size of the squares (in points). The label text size is 1/3 the size of the squares.\par
\par
To Use:\par
The script creates squares and labels for each swatch defined in the Swatches Panel, not just those used in the artwork.\par
Therefore, before running the script, use the Add Used Colors command in the Swatches Panel flyout menu to make sure\par
Swatches are defined for all used colors. Use Select All Unused and Delete Swatch commands to remove unused Swatches.\par
\par
Experimental Notes:\par
The script is titled "JET_X..." because although it is useable, I consider it a work-in-progress.\par
1. The value entered in the prompt is by default interpreted as a string, which in the first attempt,\par
caused the spacing of the squares to act wrong. The parseFloat() function is used\par
to correct that.\par
2. Future improvement: Add a dialog with radio buttons to select between:\par
All Named Swatches\par
Used Named Swatches\par
All Spot Swatches\par
Used Spot Swatches\par
Then embed this script into a function that is called when All Named Swatches is selected.\b\par
